			<item>
				<title>Update with pacman</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/update-pacman/</link>
				<pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 14:09:31 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/update-pacman/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;There are 3 commands used to update &lt;strong&gt;Endeavour OS&lt;/strong&gt; systems:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/update-pacman/#sudo-pacman--syu&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman -Syu&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/update-pacman/#yay&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;yay&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/update-pacman/#eos-update&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;eos-update&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;pacman--syu&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman -Syu&lt;/code&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;#pacman--syu&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To perform a full system update and refresh, run:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;902b365&#34; class=&#34;language-sh &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;$ sudo pacman -Syu&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;pacman&lt;/code&gt; is the package manager used to install and update programs in Arch Linux.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-info d-flex&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;flex-shrink-1 alert-icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;material-icons size-20 me-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;  info&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34;&gt;Some commands require prepending &lt;code&gt;sudo&lt;/code&gt; to them as they require &lt;code&gt;super user&lt;/code&gt; (or root) permissions to run.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example terminal output&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Re-rank Arch mirrors</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/rerank-arch-mirrors/</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:22 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/rerank-arch-mirrors/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;To re-rank EndeavourOS mirrors, follow &lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/rerank-endeavouros-mirrors/&#34;&gt;this guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview &lt;a href=&#34;#overview&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mirrors&lt;/strong&gt; are servers located around the world that store copies of software packages. When upgrading packages, your EndeavourOS system utilizes multiple mirrors, which are noted in a &lt;code&gt;mirrorlist&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A well-maintained &lt;code&gt;mirrorlist&lt;/code&gt; ensures the &lt;code&gt;pacman&lt;/code&gt; package manager can access up-to-date package files when performing system updates. Outdated mirrors can prevent &lt;code&gt;pacman&lt;/code&gt; from updating &lt;strong&gt;core packages&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-warning d-flex&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;flex-shrink-1 alert-icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;material-icons size-20 me-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;  warning&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34;&gt;It is recommended to re-rank mirrors at least every 1-2 months to maintain an up-to-date mirrorlist.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;update-mirrorlist&#34;&gt;Update mirrorlist &lt;a href=&#34;#update-mirrorlist&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Update the Arch &lt;code&gt;mirrorlist&lt;/code&gt; by running:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Re-rank EndeavourOS mirrors</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/rerank-endeavouros-mirrors/</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:22 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/rerank-endeavouros-mirrors/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;To rerank Arch mirrors, follow &lt;a href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/rerank-arch-mirrors/&#34;&gt;this guide&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endeavour OS&lt;/strong&gt; has its own distro-unique packages, which may be slightly modified versions of Arch packages.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Update the Endeavour OS &lt;code&gt;mirrorlist&lt;/code&gt; with:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;63dedcc&#34; class=&#34;language-sh &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;$ eos-rankmirrors&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-info d-flex&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;flex-shrink-1 alert-icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;material-icons size-20 me-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;  info&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34;&gt;The &lt;code&gt;eos-rankmirrors&lt;/code&gt; process only shows terminal output (no GUI tool).&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The terminal may display errors/warnings as the system tests various mirrors for connectivity and speed. It may take a few minutes to find the requisite amount of mirrors.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Why do I get errors when I try to update?</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/faqs/getting-update-errors/</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:22 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/faqs/getting-update-errors/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;Some update errors are caused by issues with mirrors and mirrorlist configurations.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;These issues can usually be fixed by re-ranking mirrors.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;See: &lt;a data-bs-delay=&#34;{&amp;#34;hide&amp;#34;:300,&amp;#34;show&amp;#34;:550}&#34; data-bs-html=&#34;true&#34; data-bs-title=&#34;&lt;a href=&#39;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/rerank-arch-mirrors/&#39;&gt;&lt;p&gt;SYSTEM MAINTENANCE&lt;/p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Re-rank Arch mirrors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Keep your Arch mirrorlist up-to-date by re-ranking mirrors.&lt;/a&gt;&#34; data-bs-toggle=&#34;tooltip&#34; href=&#34;https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/system-maintenance/rerank-arch-mirrors/&#34;&gt;Update mirrors guide&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Outdated package databases will cause errors when &lt;code&gt;pacman&lt;/code&gt; tries to retrieve the latest package files. This can be prevented through regular mirror maintenance.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;error-failed-to-commit-transaction-conflicting-files&#34;&gt;Error: failed to commit transaction (conflicting files) &lt;a href=&#34;#error-failed-to-commit-transaction-conflicting-files&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Running a &lt;code&gt;sudo pacman -Syu&lt;/code&gt; update may fail and display the following errors:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>Are there mirror management alternatives?</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/faqs/mirror-alternatives/</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:22 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/faqs/mirror-alternatives/</guid>
				<description>&lt;p&gt;Popular alternatives to mirror management are listed on the &lt;a href=&#34;https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Mirrors&#34; rel=&#34;external&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Arch mirrors wiki&lt;svg width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; d=&#34;M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Some programs can automate mirror management when configured properly.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;One such example is &lt;code&gt;ghostmirror&lt;/code&gt;, which:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title>What is the AUR?</title>
				<link>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/faqs/what-is-aur/</link>
				<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:00:22 -0700</pubDate>
				<guid>https://redzhift.github.io/docs/user-guides/faqs/what-is-aur/</guid>
				<description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;what-is-the-aur&#34;&gt;What is the AUR? &lt;a href=&#34;#what-is-the-aur&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Arch User Repository&lt;/strong&gt;, also known as &lt;strong&gt;AUR&lt;/strong&gt;, is a large library of community user-produced packages for Arch Linux.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Popular and well-maintained packages are voted on by the community to include in the official Arch &lt;em&gt;extra&lt;/em&gt; repository.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;how-do-i-download-and-install-aur-packages&#34;&gt;How do I download and install AUR packages? &lt;a href=&#34;#how-do-i-download-and-install-aur-packages&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Clone the &lt;code&gt;git&lt;/code&gt; repository listed on the package&amp;rsquo;s AUR page:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;6a1139a&#34; class=&#34;language-sh &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt; git clone https://aur.archlinux.org/&amp;lt;pkg&amp;gt;.git&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Change into the package directory:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
			</item>
	</channel>
